  "body": "**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\n\r\nI request a feature.\r\n\r\n**What is the current behavior?**\r\n\r\nCurrently, there is no Error-shaped propType option.\r\nhttps://facebook.github.io/react/docs/typechecking-with-proptypes.html\r\n\r\n**My minimal use case**\r\n\r\n```js\r\nclass MyImage extends Component {\r\n  async fetchUrl () {\r\n    try {\r\n      const src = await reqUrl(fid)\r\n      this.setState({ src })\r\n    } catch (error) {\r\n      this.setState({ error })\r\n      throw error\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  render () {\r\n    const { src, error } = this.state\r\n    return <Image src={src} error={error}  />\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n\r\nclass Image extends Component {\r\n  static propTypes = {\r\n    src: PropTypes.string,\r\n    error: PropTypes.error,   <--- my requested feature\r\n  };\r\n\r\n  render () {\r\n    const { src, error } = this.props\r\n    const _src = error ? errorSrc : src\r\n    return <img src={_src} />\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n",
